# ZAP Core Workflow Instructions

## 1. Core Operating Procedure for Anti
- ALWAYS verify the physical SQL implementation when modifying a C# entity.
- ALWAYS use MCP queries to inspect live tables before assuming column setups: `mcp_zap-gcp-postgres_query`.
- Write idempotent implementation.
- Prioritize updating `system.lookups` for dropdowns/options instead of hardcoded mappings or new tables.

## 2. Collaboration
- Act autonomously but respect the strict directory map: `d:\Working\01-Project\COMPANY\ZAP\...`
- Notify the user of any side-effects related to schema altering.
